# SSC Grammar Rules

Upload your SSC grammar rules here following this structure:

```
/content/rules/ssc/
├── completing-sentence/
│   └── rules.json
├── right-form-of-verbs/
│   └── rules.json
├── articles/
│   └── rules.json
├── prepositions/
│   └── rules.json
└── ...
```

## JSON File Format

Each rules.json file should contain:

```json
{
  "topic": "Completing Sentence",
  "rules": [
    {
      "title": "Conditional Sentences",
      "content": "Conditional sentences express hypothetical situations and their consequences...",
      "examples": [
        "If I study hard, I will pass the exam.",
        "If it rains, we will stay home.",
        "If you help me, I will help you."
      ],
      "tips": [
        "Use 'if' to introduce the condition",
        "Use future tense in the main clause",
        "Present tense in the if-clause"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```